A Magistratesâ€™ Court in Kaduna on Friday ordered that a 33-year-old man, Clement Michael, who allegedly defiled a nine-year-old girl, be remanded in a correctional facility, pending legal advice. NAN reports that the Magistrate, Umar Ibrahim Ibrahim who did not take the plea of the defendant, adjourned the matter until Feb. 21, for hearing. The police charged Michael, whose address was not given, with defilement. The Magistrate, ordered the police to duplicate the case file and forward a copy to the State Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP) for legal advice The Prosecution Counsel, Insp. Chidi Leo, had told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Jan. 10 at 1 p.m., in Malali, Kaduna State. Leo alleged that the defendant lured the nine-year-old-girl into his room and defiled her. The offence according to Insp Leo is punishable under Sections 261 of the Kaduna State Penal Code State.